desc:
From the top of the Krippenstein;
Some experience required.

1500m almost vertical rise from the valley floor.

just outside cable car station Föhn!!!  > Föhndiagramm: http://www.meteocentrale.ch/de/wetter/foehn-und-bise/foehn.html;
- Webcams: https://live.laax.com/de/webcam
- Weather: https://live.laax.com/de/wetter

- TO 'Jakobshorn Gipfel': 3min from cable car peak station; windsock on top of mountain; 
- TO 'Jatzhütte': 10min from cable car (see picture): S-SW-W; easy.
- TO 'Brämabüel': in winter by chair lift; in summer to be reached only by walking about 20min from  the Jakobshorn peak

- TO 'North': 5min from Gondola station; windsock; summer and winter; easy; with moderate N-winds dynamic soaring possible; 
Route of flight: via 'Gotschnagrat' to LZ 'Klosters'
- TO 'South': between gondola station and restaurant; summer and winter; DIFFICULT! - only for experienved pilots; Route of flight: LZ 'Davos -Bolgen'

steep, grassy meadow;
also suitable for beginners
>> do NOT park your car in the village! do NOT fly with WEST wind!

 Not recommended with WEST-winds;
Prohibited with NORD-winds ('Mistral')!!!

On the FFVL-frequency, the wind from Trainon is transmitted about every 10-15min

Two take-offs on each side of the 'col des Aravis' pass :
- south at the top of the Etale lift ; west or east ;
- north on the different ski slopes ; any open lift in summer ?

2 TO's available:
- 'Prenn' (1380m): steep -at the middle station of the 'Hirzer'-gondola;
- 'Klammeben': about 20min walk from topstation of gondola

large meadow with some stones;
20 min walk (or 4WD) from end of paved road.
HG normally use Mte. Ariola: 41°21'35.6''N, 14°25'0.2''E (1150m)

Main Wind direction: S-SW; 
NOT good in W
Eventually flyable in LIGHT (!) NE

Just a few minutes from 'Rifugio Perugia';
wide open, grassy.
This is just one TO-option; other possibilities can be found nearby or along the small track leaving from Rif.Perugia...

cleared patch just below road/ parking;
no wind sock/ streamers... Wind direction: anything more than NNE is no good;
LZ: if it is thermic, thermals will release out of the river bed just in front of LZ, making approach/ landing bumpy/ difficult.

